  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AppUtil
    AppUtil contains a few utilities related to application and activity management.
    AppUtil.DialogContext  
    Assert
    Assert is a utility class for assertions that generates an exception which gets written to the log, but then continues on with the application.
    CallbackRegistrar<T>
    A helper class for managing registration of notification callbacks
    Deadline
    Deadline enhances ElapsedTime with an explicit duration.
    DebuggableReentrantLock
    DebuggableReentrantLock is a ReentrantLock with additional capabilities that help facilitate debugging
    Dom2XmlPullBuilder
    Simplistic DOM2 builder that should be enough to do support most cases.
    FrequentErrorReporter<T>
    FrequentErrorReporter is a little utility that suppresses runs of the same error so as to avoid flooding logs
    PreferencesHelper
    A little utility to help with the generic reading and writing of preferences
    PreferencesHelper.StringMap  
    ReusableCountDownLatch
    This is nothing more than a clone of CountDownLatch that additionally allows the count to be reset.
    ReusableCountDownLatch.Sync  
    RobotApplication
    RobotApplication exists to avail ourselves of the ability to initialize some system structures at a very early state in the application launch sequence, before any of the rest of our code might have seen them in an uninitialized state.
    ServiceController
    ServiceController provides control of and auto-starting for services
    ServiceController.AutoStartableService  
    StartableService
    StartableService provides the framework of a startable service on top of the instantiation of a closeable object
    SystemProperties
    SystemProperties provides access to android.os.SystemProperties
    WatchdogMonitor
    WatchdogMonitor is a simple class that will fire an action after a certain interval if not cancelled first.
